Introduction¶

I have extracted snippet's of code from a project I have been working on to create a relatively simple investment strategy based on tactical asset allocation towards different asset classes primarily in the forms of ETFs. Personally, I am not a huge fan of advocating backtests and will be the first to tell you that there is room for improvement - this is at best a first stage prototype which has multiple layers of potential overfitting and statistical oversights. That being said, it's my first real attempt at putting into production a framework for dynamic asset allocation and hopefully will hold the foundations for future improvement.

The strategy uses Yahoo Finance price data to construct a dual momentum signal within each asset class. Dual momentum is traditionally done by comparing the cross-section (XMOM) of regional buckets and picking the highest trending exposure contingent on positive time-series momentum (TSMOM). I have adapted this to perform XMOM on high-beta vs low-beta instruments instead to discriminate on cyclicality of returns as opposed to country specific bets. I have also adapted to certain idiosyncrasies relating to asset classes when I have felt it is fair and reasonable to do so. For example, looking at past price data for volatility related instruments would not be as relevant as using the VIX Index directly for evaluating market related movements in that particular asset class.

There are many different facets of this ongoing project in which I could continue to elaborate but at this point, I believe it would be remiss to do so. Like Ithaka, I would prefer this to remain a destination with unknown unknowns that I will hopefully edge towards progressively. With that, feel free to run the notebook and provide comments / suggestions - eager to hear from others embarking on a similar journey.

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import math
from datetime import date, datetime
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.dates import YearLocator
import seaborn as sns
import warnings

warnings.simplefilter(action='ignore', category=FutureWarning)

class MomentumStrategy(object):
    """
    Construct momentum signals based on relative return profile of underlying assets
    
    Parameters:
        tickerList - list of tickers composing risky assets
        riskTicker - ticker of instrument used for risk indicator signal
        cashTicker - ticker of risk-free asset
        startDate - start date of backtest
        endDate - end date of backtest
        momentumLookback - lookback period in months used to produce momentum signal
        riskLookback - lookback period in months used to produce risk indicator signal
        signalFrequency - number of days before signals are refreshed
        
    Methods:
        getPrices()- retrieves historical price data from mySQL database for input ticker
        getReturns() - returns daily asset returns for input ticker
        getSignalsUpdate() - returns signal update indicator based on signalFrequency
        getSignals() - returns momentum signal for a given lookback period on tickerList
        getRiskIndicator() - returns risk on/off indicator for a given lookback period on riskTicker
        getCashReturns() - returns daily risk-free asset returns
        getSignalWeights() - returns historical signals for each instrument traded
        getTradeCount() - returns number of signal changes for each instrument traded
        getStrategyReturns() - returns daily strategy returns
        getStrategyCurve() -  returns cumulative strategy returns
    
    """
    
    def __init__(self, tickerList, riskTicker, cashTicker, startDate, endDate, momentumLookback, riskLookback, signalFrequency, leverageRatio):
        self.tickerList = tickerList
        self.riskTicker = riskTicker
        self.cashTicker = cashTicker
        self.startDate = startDate
        self.endDate = endDate
        self.momentumLookback = momentumLookback
        self.riskLookback = riskLookback
        self.signalFrequency = signalFrequency
        self.leverageRatio = leverageRatio
    
    def getPrices(self, tickers):
        priceData = pd.DataFrame(yf.download(tickers, start="2000-01-01", end=date.today(), progress=False)['Adj Close'])
        if len(tickers) == 1:
            priceData.columns = tickers
        return priceData
    
    def getPricesGBP(self, tickers):
        priceData = self.getPrices(tickers)
        currencyData = pd.DataFrame(1, index=priceData.index, columns=priceData.columns)
        tickersUSD = ['CNDX.L','SPMV.L','IHYA.L','LQDA.L','TBF','VIXL.L','UUP','FTFX.L','GSG','GLD']
        for ticker in tickersUSD:
            if ticker in currencyData.columns:
                currencyData[ticker] = self.getPrices(['GBP=X'])
        priceData = priceData.multiply(currencyData).dropna()
        return priceData
    
    def getReturns(self, tickers):
        priceData = self.getPricesGBP(tickers)
        returnsData = priceData.pct_change(1)
        return returnsData
    
    def getSignalsUpdate(self):
        self.priceData = self.getPrices(self.tickerList)
        self.signalsUpdate = pd.Series(0, index=self.priceData.index)
        self.signalsUpdate.iloc[::self.signalFrequency] = 1
        return self.signalsUpdate
    
    def getSignals(self, tradeLag):
        self.signalsUpdate = self.getSignalsUpdate()
        self.momReturn = self.priceData.rolling(window=5).mean().pct_change(21 * self.momentumLookback)
        self.signalData = self.momReturn.eq(self.momReturn.max(1),axis=0).astype(int).shift(tradeLag).where(self.signalsUpdate==1).ffill().where(self.momReturn.notna().all(axis=1))
        return self.signalData
    
    def getRiskIndicator(self, tradeLag):
        self.signalsUpdate = self.getSignalsUpdate()
        if self.riskTicker != None:
            self.riskBench = self.getPrices([self.riskTicker])
            self.riskIndicator = pd.Series(0, index=self.riskBench.index)
            if self.riskTicker == '^VIX':
                self.rollingQuantiles = self.riskBench.rolling(window=21*self.riskLookback, center=False).quantile(0.99)
                self.riskIndicator = (self.riskBench < self.rollingQuantiles).astype(int).shift(tradeLag).where(self.signalsUpdate == 1).ffill()
            else:
                self.riskIndicator = (self.riskBench.rolling(window=5).mean().pct_change(21 * self.riskLookback) > 0).astype(int).shift(tradeLag).where(self.signalsUpdate==1).ffill()
            self.riskIndicator = pd.Series(self.riskIndicator.iloc[:,0])
        else:
            self.riskIndicator = 1
        return self.riskIndicator
    
    def getCashReturns(self, tradeLag):
        self.cashSignal = self.getRiskIndicator(tradeLag).replace({0: 1, 1: 0}) if self.riskTicker is not None else 0
        self.cashPrice = pd.Series(self.getPrices([self.cashTicker]).iloc[:,0])
        self.cashReturn = self.cashPrice.pct_change(1) * self.cashSignal
        return self.cashReturn
    
    def getSignalWeights(self, tradeLag):
        if self.riskTicker != None:
            self.getCashReturns(tradeLag)
            self.cashSignal = self.cashSignal.rename(self.cashTicker)
            self.signalData = self.getSignals(tradeLag).where(self.cashSignal == 0, 0)
            self.referenceWeights = pd.concat([self.signalData,self.cashSignal], axis=1)
        else:
            self.referenceWeights = self.getSignals(tradeLag)
        return self.referenceWeights
    
    def getTradeCount(self):
        self.tradeCount = self.getSignalWeights(2).diff().ne(0)
        return self.tradeCount
    
    def getLeverageCosts(self):
        self.leverageCosts = (self.leverageRatio-1) * self.getReturns(['ERNS.L']).iloc[:,0]
        return self.leverageCosts
    
    def getSpreadCosts(self):
        self.spreadCosts = self.leverageRatio * self.getTradeCount().astype(int).sum(axis=1) * 0.0005
        return self.spreadCosts
        
    def getTCosts(self):
        self.tCosts = self.getLeverageCosts() + self.getSpreadCosts()
        return self.tCosts
    
    def getStrategyReturns(self):
        self.strategyReturns = (self.leverageRatio * self.getRiskIndicator(2) * (self.getSignals(2) * self.getReturns(self.tickerList)).sum(axis=1) + self.getCashReturns(2).where(self.momReturn.notna().all(axis=1))).sub(self.getTCosts())
        return self.strategyReturns
    
    def getStrategyCurve(self):
        self.strategyReturns = self.getStrategyReturns()
        self.strategyCurve = 100 * (1 + self.strategyReturns).cumprod()
        return self.strategyCurve
    

class Benchmark(MomentumStrategy):    
    """
    Create benchmark for momentum strategy
    
    Parameters:
        benchTicker - ticker of benchmark asset
        startDate - start date of backtest
        endDate - end date of backtest 
        
    Methods:
        getBenchmarkCurve - returns cumulative returns of benchmark

    """
    
    def __init__(self, benchTicker, startDate, endDate):
        self.benchTicker = benchTicker
        self.startDate = startDate
        self.endDate = endDate
     
    def getBenchmarkCurve(self):
        self.benchmarkCurve = 100 * (1 + self.getReturns(self.benchTicker)).cumprod().iloc[:,0]
        return self.benchmarkCurve
    
    
class StrategyStats(Benchmark):
    """
    Aggregate generalized performance statistics for strategy and benchmark
    
    Parameters:
        df - cumulative returns of strategy
        bm - cumulative returns of  benchmark
        
    Methods:
        getComparisonCurve - returns single Dataframe with strategy/benchmark cumulative returns
        getAnnReturn() - returns annualized return of strategy/benchmark
        getAnnVol() - returns annalized volatility of strategy/benchmark
        getSharpe() - returns Sharpe ratio of strategy/benchmark
        getMaxDrawdown() - returns maximum daily drawdown of strategy/benchmark
        getMaxDrawdownDuration() - returns maximum daily drawdown duration of strategy/benchmark
        getCalmar() - returns Calmar ratio of strategy/benchmark
        plotCurve() - produces a plot of strategy/benchmark cumulative returns
        printSummary() - displays full summary statistics of strategy/benchmark
    
    """
    
    def __init__(self, df, bm):
        self.df = df
        self.bm = bm
        
    def getComparisonCurve(self):
        self.comparisonReturns = pd.concat([self.df, self.bm], axis=1).dropna().pct_change(1)
        self.comparisonCurve = 100 * (1 + self.comparisonReturns).cumprod()
        self.comparisonCurve.iloc[0] = 100
        self.comparisonCurve = self.comparisonCurve.rename(columns={self.comparisonCurve.columns[0]: "Strategy" })
        return self.comparisonCurve
        
    def getAnnReturn(self):
        self.comparisonCurve = self.getComparisonCurve()
        self.annReturn = [((self.comparisonCurve[col][-1] / self.comparisonCurve[col].loc[self.comparisonCurve[col].first_valid_index()]) ** (365 / (self.comparisonCurve[col].index[-1] - self.comparisonCurve[col].first_valid_index()).days)) - 1 for col in self.comparisonCurve]
        return self.annReturn
    
    def getAnnVol(self):
        self.comparisonCurve = self.getComparisonCurve()
        self.annVol = [math.sqrt(252) * self.comparisonCurve[col].pct_change(1).std() for col in self.comparisonCurve]
        return self.annVol
    
    def getSharpe(self):
        self.annReturn = self.getAnnReturn()
        self.annVol = self.getAnnVol()
        self.sharpeRatio = [returnVal / volVal for returnVal, volVal in zip(self.annReturn, self.annVol)]
        return self.sharpeRatio
    
    def getDailyDrawdown(self):
        self.dailyDrawdown = self.getComparisonCurve() / self.getComparisonCurve().cummax() - 1
        return self.dailyDrawdown
    
    def getMaxDrawdown(self):
        self.comparisonCurve = self.getComparisonCurve()
        self.maxDrawdown = [(1 - self.comparisonCurve[col].div(self.comparisonCurve[col].cummax())).expanding().max().max() for col in self.comparisonCurve]
        return self.maxDrawdown
    
    def getMaxDrawdownDuration(self):
        self.comparisonCurve = self.getComparisonCurve()
        self.maxDrawdownDuration = []
        for col in self.comparisonCurve:
            self.drawdown = 1 - self.comparisonCurve[col].div(self.comparisonCurve[col].cummax())
            self.drawdownDuration = []
            self.currentDuration = 0
            for val in self.drawdown:
                if val != 0:
                    self.currentDuration += 1
                else:
                    self.currentDuration = 0
                self.drawdownDuration.append(self.currentDuration)
            self.maxDrawdownDuration.append(max(self.drawdownDuration))
        return self.maxDrawdownDuration
    
    def getCalmar(self):
        self.annReturn = self.getAnnReturn()
        self.maxDrawdown = self.getMaxDrawdown()
        self.calmarRatio = [returnVal / ddVal for returnVal, ddVal in zip(self.annReturn, self.maxDrawdown)]
        return self.calmarRatio
    
    def plotCurve(self):
        self.getComparisonCurve()
        sns.lineplot(self.comparisonCurve)
        plt.xlabel('Date')
        plt.show()
        
    def printSummary(self):
        self.getSharpe()
        self.getCalmar()
        self.getMaxDrawdownDuration()
        print('------------------------------------------------------------------')
        print('The Annualized Return of the strategy is',"{0:.1%}".format(self.annReturn[0]))
        print('The Annualized Volatility of the strategy is',"{0:.1%}".format(self.annVol[0])) 
        print('The Maximum Drawdown of the strategy is',"{0:.1%}".format(self.maxDrawdown[0]))     
        print('The Maximum Drawdown Duration of the strategy is',round(self.maxDrawdownDuration[0]/21,0),'months')
        print('The Sharpe Ratio of the strategy is',round(self.sharpeRatio[0],2))
        print('The Calmar Ratio of the strategy is',round(self.calmarRatio[0],2))
        print('------------------------------------------------------------------')
        print('The Annualized Return of the benchmark is',"{0:.1%}".format(self.annReturn[1])) 
        print('The Annualized Volatility of the benchmark is',"{0:.1%}".format(self.annVol[1])) 
        print('The Maximum Drawdown of the benchmark is',"{0:.1%}".format(self.maxDrawdown[1]))
        print('The Maximum Drawdown Duration of the benchmark is',round(self.maxDrawdownDuration[1]/21,0),'months')
        print('The Sharpe Ratio of the benchmark is', round(self.sharpeRatio[1],2))
        print('The Calmar Ratio of the benchmark is',round(self.calmarRatio[1],2))
        print('------------------------------------------------------------------')


class Portfolio(StrategyStats):
    """
    Create composite class for MomentumStrategy and StrategyStats
    
    Parameters:
        tickerList - list of tickers composing risky assets
        riskTicker - ticker of instrument used for risk indicator signal
        cashTicker - ticker of risk-free asset
        startDate - start date of backtest
        endDate - end date of backtest
        momentumLookback - lookback period used to produce momentum signal
        riskLookback - lookback period used to produce risk indicator signal
        benchTicker - ticker of benchmark asset
        signalFrequency - number of days before signals are refreshed
        
    Methods:
        getPortfolio - instantiates MomentumStrategy and StrategyStats classes
        
    """
    
    def __init__(self, tickerList, riskTicker, cashTicker, startDate, endDate, momentumLookback, riskLookback, benchTicker, signalFrequency, leverageRatio):
        self.tickerList = tickerList
        self.riskTicker = riskTicker
        self.cashTicker = cashTicker
        self.startDate = startDate
        self.endDate = endDate
        self.momentumLookback = momentumLookback
        self.riskLookback = riskLookback
        self.benchTicker = benchTicker
        self.signalFrequency = signalFrequency
        self.leverageRatio = leverageRatio
    
    def getPortfolio(self):
        self.portfolio = MomentumStrategy(self.tickerList, self.riskTicker, self.cashTicker, self.startDate, self.endDate, self.momentumLookback, self.riskLookback, self.signalFrequency, self.leverageRatio)
        self.bm = Benchmark(self.benchTicker, self.startDate, self.endDate)
        self.portfolioStats = StrategyStats(self.portfolio.getStrategyCurve(), self.bm.getBenchmarkCurve())
        return self.portfolioStats
    
    
class AggregatePortfolio(Portfolio):
    
    """
    Aggregates two or more strategies into a single rebalanced strategy based on target weights
    
    Parameters:
        inputCurves - cumulative returns on input strategies
        targetWeights - inital and rebalance weights of input strategies
        rebalanceFrequency - number of months before portfolio is rebalanced to targetWeights
        
    Methods:
        getAggregateReturns() - returns DataFrame of cumulative returns based on inputCurves
        getRebalanceSignals() - returns rebalance signals based on rebalanceFrequency
        getDriftedWeights() - returns drifted weights of aggregated strategy based on inital target weights and market drift
        getAggregateCurve() - returns cumulative returns of aggregated strategy based on drifted weights
    
    """
    
    def __init__(self, inputCurves, targetWeights, rebalanceFrequency):
        self.inputCurves = inputCurves
        self.targetWeights = targetWeights
        self.rebalanceFrequency = rebalanceFrequency

    def getAggregateReturns(self):
        self.aggregateReturns = pd.concat(self.inputCurves, axis=1).dropna()
        return self.aggregateReturns
    
    def getRebalanceSignals(self):
        self.aggregateReturns = self.getAggregateReturns()
        self.rebalanceSignals = pd.Series(0, index=self.aggregateReturns.index)
        self.rebalanceSignals.iloc[::21*self.rebalanceFrequency] = 1
        return self.rebalanceSignals
    
    def getDriftedWeights(self):
        self.rebalanceSignals = self.getRebalanceSignals()
        self.driftedWeights = pd.DataFrame(self.targetWeights, index=self.aggregateReturns.index)
        for i in range(1,len(self.driftedWeights)):
            if self.rebalanceSignals.iloc[i] == 1:
                self.driftedWeights.iloc[i] = self.targetWeights
            else:
                self.driftedWeights.iloc[i] = self.driftedWeights.iloc[i-1].values*(1+self.aggregateReturns.iloc[i-1].values) / (self.driftedWeights.iloc[i-1].values*(1+self.aggregateReturns.iloc[i-1].values)).sum()
        return self.driftedWeights
        
    def getAggregateCurve(self):
        self.driftedWeights = self.getDriftedWeights()
        self.driftedReturns = pd.DataFrame((self.aggregateReturns.values * self.driftedWeights.values).sum(axis=1))
        self.aggregateCurve = pd.DataFrame(100 * (1+self.driftedReturns).cumprod())
        self.aggregateCurve.index = self.aggregateReturns.index
        return self.aggregateCurve

            portfolioInput = {

                'commodity': [['GSG','GLD'],None,'ERNS.L',startDate,endDate,lookback,xlookback,['GSG'],signalFrequency,leverageRatio],
                'crypto': [['BTC-GBP'],'BTC-GBP','ERNS.L',startDate,endDate,lookback,xlookback,['BTC-GBP'],signalFrequency,leverageRatio],
                'rates': [['VUTY.L','TBF'],None,'ERNS.L',startDate,endDate,lookback,xlookback,['VUTY.L'],signalFrequency,leverageRatio],
                'volatility': [['CNDX.L'],'^VIX','VIXL.L',startDate,endDate,lookback,xlookback,['VIXL.L'],signalFrequency,leverageRatio],
                'fx': [['UUP'],'UUP','ERNS.L',startDate,endDate,lookback,xlookback,['UUP'],signalFrequency,leverageRatio]
            }
        
            print('------------------------------------------------------------------')
            portfolioCurves = []
            portfolios = []
        
            for portfolioName, portfolioData in portfolioInput.items():
                print('Building',portfolioName,'portfolio...')
                portfolio = Portfolio(*portfolioData)
                portfolioCurve = portfolio.getStrategyReturns()
                portfolioCurves.append(portfolioCurve)
                portfolios.append(portfolio)
        
            print('Building aggregate portfolio...')
            aggregatePortfolio = AggregatePortfolio(portfolioCurves,rebalanceWeights,frequency)
            combinedCurve = aggregatePortfolio.getAggregateCurve()
            combinedPortfolioStats = StrategyStats(combinedCurve, portfolios[0].getBenchmarkCurve())
            #sharpeOutput[xlookback, frequency, lookback] = {(combinedPortfolioStats.getSharpe()[0])}
            combinedPortfolioStats.printSummary()
        
""" Retrieve instrument-level weights """
portfolioKey = {portfolio: name for portfolio, name in zip(portfolios, ['equity', 'credit', 'commodity', 'crypto', 'rates', 'volatility','fx'])}
combinedDriftedWeights = aggregatePortfolio.getDriftedWeights()

effectiveWeights = [
    portfolio.getSignalWeights(2)
    .loc[portfolio.getSignalWeights(2).index.isin(combinedDriftedWeights.index)]
    .multiply(combinedDriftedWeights[portfolioKey[portfolio]], axis=0)
    for portfolio in portfolios
]

combinedEffectiveWeights = pd.concat(effectiveWeights, axis=1).dropna()
combinedEffectiveWeights = combinedEffectiveWeights.groupby(combinedEffectiveWeights.columns, axis=1).sum()

targetWeights = [
    portfolio.getSignalWeights(0)
    .loc[portfolio.getSignalWeights(0).index.isin(combinedDriftedWeights.index)]
    .multiply(combinedDriftedWeights[portfolioKey[portfolio]], axis=0)
    for portfolio in portfolios
]

combinedTargetWeights = pd.concat(targetWeights, axis=1).dropna()
combinedTargetWeights = combinedTargetWeights.groupby(combinedTargetWeights.columns, axis=1).sum()

""" Retrieve number of instrument-level trades """
portfolioTrades = [
    pd.DataFrame(portfolio.getTradeCount()
    .loc[portfolio.getTradeCount().index.isin(combinedDriftedWeights.index)])
    .sum() / ((combinedCurve.index[-1]-combinedCurve.index[0]).days/365)
    for portfolio in portfolios
]

portfolioTrades = pd.DataFrame(portfolioTrades).sum()

def getRollingSharpe(strategyCurve, window):
    rollingReturn = strategyCurve.rolling(window).mean()
    rollingVolatility = strategyCurve.rolling(window).std()
    rollingSharpe = (rollingReturn / rollingVolatility) * np.sqrt(window)
    return rollingSharpe

def getMonthlyReturns(strategyCurve):
    monthlyReturns = (1 + strategyCurve.pct_change(1)).resample('M').prod() - 1
    monthlyReturns = monthlyReturns.reset_index().pivot_table(index=monthlyReturns.index.year, columns=monthlyReturns.index.month, values=strategyCurve.pct_change(1).columns[0])
    return monthlyReturns

def getStrategyVisuals():
    titles = ['equity', 'credit', 'commodity', 'crypto', 'rates', 'volatility', 'fx']
    non_empty_portfolios = [portfolio for portfolio in portfolios if not getMonthlyReturns(pd.DataFrame(portfolio.getStrategyCurve())).empty]
    num_non_empty_portfolios = len(non_empty_portfolios)
    rows = 3
    cols = 3
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(rows, cols, figsize=(12, 10))
    for idx, (portfolio, title) in enumerate(zip(non_empty_portfolios, titles)):
        data = getMonthlyReturns(pd.DataFrame(portfolio.getStrategyCurve()))
        data = data[data.index >= 2018]
        row = idx // cols
        col = idx % cols
        sns.heatmap(data.T * 100, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', fmt=".1f", annot_kws={"size": 8}, ax=axes[row, col])
        axes[row, col].set_xlabel('Years')
        axes[row, col].set_ylabel('Months')
        axes[row, col].set_title(title)
    for i in range(num_non_empty_portfolios, rows * cols):
        fig.delaxes(axes[i // cols, i % cols])
    plt.tight_layout()

getStrategyVisuals()

def getPerfAttribution():
    perfAttribution = pd.DataFrame(aggregatePortfolio.aggregateReturns.values * aggregatePortfolio.driftedWeights.values, columns=rebalanceWeights.keys(), index=aggregatePortfolio.aggregateReturns.index)[liveDate:].sum(axis=0)
    ax = sns.barplot(x=perfAttribution.index, y=perfAttribution.values*100, palette="viridis")
    ax.text(0.95, 0.95, f'Total: {round(perfAttribution.sum()*100,1)}%', transform=ax.transAxes, color='black', ha='right', va='top')
    plt.title('Live Performance Attribution')
    plt.ylabel('Period Return (%)')
    plt.show()
